  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1679580317073-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1679580317073-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1679580317073-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1679580317073-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1679580317073-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a baking tray (or two!), with a drizzle of<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>olive oil</strong> and season with your <strong>dried oregano</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 25 min or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>herby potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679580324941-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679580324941-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679580324941-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679580324941-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1679580324941-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>chicken breast portion[s] </strong>to a plate with your<strong> cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Refrigerate until later</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1679580333576-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1679580333576-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1679580333576-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1679580333576-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1679580333576-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> sliced spring onion</strong> to a bowl with your<strong> mayo</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(not a big garlic fan? Try using less!), <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>– this is your <strong>garlic mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1679580341328-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1679580341328-x400.jpg",
